00:00:05,240 --> 00:00:12,640
Chinese President Xi Jinping has unveiled a new initiative aimed at creating a more inclusive international order.

3
00:00:12,640 --> 00:00:20,559
President Xi used his address and the Shanghai Cooperation Organization Plus meeting in Tianjin to launch the Global Governance Initiative.

4
00:00:20,559 --> 00:00:32,520
He urged member states to lead the way in shaping a fairer world order, which is based on such guiding principles and sovereign equality, international law and multilateralism.

5
00:00:32,520 --> 00:00:37,079
We should adhere to sovereign equality.

6
00:00:37,079 --> 00:00:47,840
We should maintain that all countries, regardless of size, strength and wealth, are equal participants, decision makers and beneficiaries in global governance.

7
00:00:47,840 --> 00:00:56,359
We should promote greater democracy in international relations and increase the representation and voice of developing countries.

8
00:00:56,359 --> 00:01:12,599
The Chinese president also announced a series of new platforms for China-SCO cooperation, including partnerships in energy, green industry and the digital economy, along with centers for scientific innovation, higher education and vocational training.

9
00:01:12,599 --> 00:01:22,719
He pledged to expand the region's renewable energy capacity and proposed deeper collaboration in artificial intelligence, satellite navigation and lunar exploration.

10
00:01:24,359 --> 00:01:33,800
Chinese President Xi Jinping has urged member countries of the Shanghai Cooperation Organization to march toward modernization by working together for a shared future.

11
00:01:33,800 --> 00:01:44,880
In his keynote speech on the SEO Council of Hezhar State in Tianjin, President Xi highlighted the Shanghai spirit that emphasizes mutual trust, equality and respect.

12
00:01:44,880 --> 00:01:50,400
He urged all members to seek common ground and pursue mutual benefit for a better future.

13
00:01:50,400 --> 00:02:03,920
The Shanghai Cooperation Organization has grown into the world's largest regional organization with a participation of 26 countries and a combined economic output of nearly $30 trillion.

14
00:02:03,920 --> 00:02:07,320
Leaders on the summit have released the Tianjin Declaration.

15
00:02:07,320 --> 00:02:13,520
They also approved a new development strategy outlining the SEO's goals for the next decade.

16
00:02:13,520 --> 00:02:23,159
The summit marked the launch of four new centers dedicated to combating security threats, transnational crimes, cyber threats and drug trafficking.

17
00:02:23,159 --> 00:02:34,879
The leaders also issued statements commemorating the 80th anniversary of victory in World War II and the founding of the United Nations and devoid their support for the multilateral trading system.

18
00:02:34,879 --> 00:02:46,679
The summit adopted 24 outcome documents focusing on enhancing cooperation in security, the economy, cultural ties and institutional development.

19
00:02:46,680 --> 00:02:55,680
The Shenzhen Hong Kong Guangzhou Innovation Cluster in southern China has taken the top ranking among the world's 100 leading innovation clusters.

20
00:02:55,680 --> 00:03:02,240
The World Intellectual Property Organization has released the 2025 Global Innovation Index.

21
00:03:02,240 --> 00:03:11,439
This is the first time the cluster has surpassed the Tokyo Yokohama cluster in Japan to become the world's leading innovation hub.

22
00:03:11,439 --> 00:03:17,520
Officials say the number of deaths from a powerful earthquake in eastern Afghanistan has exceeded 800.

23
00:03:17,520 --> 00:03:25,320
A spokesperson for the Afghan government also says the quake has left more than 2,800 others injured.

24
00:03:25,320 --> 00:03:34,640
Rescue teams are navigating remote areas with limited communication to assess the full extent of the damage and provide aid.

25
00:03:34,640 --> 00:03:42,960
Former Czech Prime Minister Andrei Babish says he's canceled his election campaign for Tuesday after being attacked during a rally.

26
00:03:42,960 --> 00:03:52,960
Babish, the leader of the opposition ANO party, was struck in the head with a metallic forum crutch by a man during an election rally on Monday afternoon.

27
00:03:52,960 --> 00:03:58,560
Czech police said officers detained the man after the attack in the eastern town of Dubra.

28
00:03:58,560 --> 00:04:05,760
The Czech Republic is set to hold elections to the lower house of the parliament in early October.

29
00:04:05,760 --> 00:04:13,400
A senior EU official says the European Union will continue to enforce its digital rules despite U.S. criticism.

30
00:04:13,400 --> 00:04:22,519
European Commission Executive Vice President Hannah Vierkunen said the rules apply equally to all companies providing services in the EU.

31
00:04:22,519 --> 00:04:36,600
U.S. President Donald Trump warned on Tuesday that his country would impose substantial additional tariffs and export restrictions on countries that adopt digital taxes or regulations targeting U.S. tech giants.

32
